text.section:
The following do not require the negotiation of a new rental-purchase agreement:
The addition or return of rental property under a multiple-item agreement or the substitution of the rental property, if in either case the average payment allocable to a payment period is not changed by more than 25 percent;
A deferral or extension of 1 or more rental payments, or portions of a rental payment;
A reduction in charges in the rental-purchase agreement; or
A rental-purchase agreement involved in a court proceeding.
